      <description>I am an environmental data scientist specialized in assessing sustainability of households, cities, and countries. At the Heidelberg Institute for Geoinformation Technology, I quantify and map pollution and greenhouse gas emissions, and assess cities&amp;rsquo; progress toward sustainable mobility, efficient land use, and biodiversity protection.
My interest in data-driven indicators to inform environmental policy started during my work as the research director of the 2024 Environmental Performance Index at the Yale Center of Environmental Law and Policy.</description>
